# STATIC RULES

## Project
- **Name:** NORAM Adjust (NORAMAdjust)
- **Game:** Nuclear Option (NO), Unity, Steam
- **Stack:** C# / .NET 4.8, NOLoader (`INOMod`) + BepInEx 5 plugin (shared core)
- **mod id:** `com.at747.noramadjust`
- **Solution:** `NORAMAdjust.sln`
- **Deploy path (NOLoader):** `Nuclear Option\NOLoader\mods\NORAMAdjust\`
- **Deploy path (BepInEx):** `Nuclear Option\BepInEx\plugins\com.at747.noramadjust\`
- **Sibling dep:** `../NOLoader_Engine` (NOLoader.API, NOLoader.ModConfig)
- **GitHub:** https://github.com/Mursisru/NORAMAdjust
- **GITHUB local:** `C:\Users\at747\Desktop\GITHUB local\NORAMAdjust\`

## Mod scope
- Reserves **5300 MB** managed RAM (`byte[]` reservoir) at load
- Active **always** (solo / host / dedicated client)
- **Do not combine** with MpClientOpt `memory_budget=1` (~double reservation)
- **Do not combine** NOLoader + BepInEx in same game install

## Code style
- Guard clauses; `_camelCase` for private static fields
- No GC alloc in hot paths (mod does not use tick API)
- GitHub documentation — **English**

## Deploy (assistant)
- NOLoader: `.\scripts\deploy-noram-adjust-mod.ps1` (game closed; no PatchTool)
- BepInEx: `.\scripts\deploy-noram-adjust-bepinex.ps1`
- **Commit/push** — only on explicit user request

## Architecture
| Class | Role |
|-------|------|
| `NoramAdjustMod` | INOMod entry; OnLoad/Unload |
| `NoramAdjustPlugin` | BepInEx entry; Awake/OnDestroy |
| `RamReservoir` | byte[] chunks, Apply/Release |
| `NoramConfig` | mod.ini: enabled, memory_reservoir_mb, chunk_mb |

See `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.

